o%20gold%2C%20real%20estate%2C%20and%20the%20agriculture%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Bloomberg's%20ETFs%20in%20Depth%20conference%20in%20Manhattan%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Roubini%20laid%20out%20a%20multi-part%20argument%20for%20why%20he%20sees%20inflation%20soaring%20to%205-6%25%20over%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%202020s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20supply%20side%20of%20the%20inflation%20equation%2C%20there%20are%20trends%20that%20should%20constrict%20the%20supply%20of%20goods%2C%20according%20to%20Roubini%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EClimate%20change%20will%20make%20food%20and%20housing%20more%20sparse%2C%20as%20higher%20temperatures%20make%20some%20areas%20of%20the%20country%20un-farmable%20and%20cause%20large%20migrations.%20Housing%20market%20struggles%20are%20already%20underway%20to%20a%20degree%20as%20insurance%20firms%20increasingly%20refuse%20to%20offer%20policies%20for%20coastal%20homes%20in%20some%20states.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReshoring%20and%20de-globalization%20trends%20as%20firms%20seek%20stability%20will%20drive%20up%20labor%20and%20goods%20costs.%20Tariffs%20will%20also%20lead%20to%20higher%20prices.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20population%20is%20aging%2C%20meaning%20fewer%20people%20will%20be%20producing%20goods%20and%20providing%20services.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDeportation%20of%20migrants%20will%20shrink%20the%20labor%20force%2C%20lowering%20the%20supply%20of%20goods%20and%20services.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20demand%20side%20of%20things%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20aging%20population%20will%20spend%20their%20savings%20as%20they%20get%20older%2C%20all%20while%20there%20are%20fewer%20young%20people%20to%20produce.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERising%20geopolitical%20risks%20mean%20higher%20government%20defense%20spending.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMore%20government%20spending%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20necessary%20to%20compensate%20for%20people%20potentially%20losing%20jobs%20to%20automation.%20And%20to%20help%20reduce%20their%20debts%2C%20governments%20will%20attempt%20to%20inflate%20away%20their%20balances.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e19c78f4-6ca3-498d-af49-74861b60b392%5C%22%3EWhat%20this%20means%20for%20markets%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20a%20scenario%20where%20inflation%20sees%20a%20resurgence%2C%20Roubini%20warned%20of%20fairly%20dire%20consequences%20for%20investors%20and%20the%20classic%20portfolio%20structure%20of%2060%25%20and%2040%25%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%2010-year%20Tresasury%20yields%20would%20soar%2C%20he%20said%2C%20as%20investors%20demand%20higher%20returns.%20That%20would%20mean%20the%20assets%20lose%20a%20large%20chunk%20of%20their%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuppose%20that%20over%20the%20next%20few%20years%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20decade%2C%20inflation%20were%20to%20be%20not%202%25%2C%20but%20say%205-6%25.%20What%20would%20be%20the%20bond%20yield%20on%20a%2010-year%20Treasury%3F%20It%20would%20have%20to%20be%20something%20like%208%25%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSix%20percent%20for%20expected%20inflation%2C%20and%202%25%20real.%20Why%202%25%20real%2C%20rather%20than%20lower%3F%20Because%20fundamental%20factors%20including%20high%20debts%20and%20deficits%20imply%20the%20risk%20premium%20lies%20closer%20to%202%25%20rather%20than%200%25.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20yields%20on%20the%2010-year%20spike%20that%20high%2C%20it%20tends%20to%20mean%20trouble%20for%20stocks%2C%20particularly%20growth%20names%2C%20which%20dominate%20the%20market%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20short%20rise%20in%20bond%20yields%20should%20lead%20to%20a%20significant%20correction%20in%20equities%2C%26quot%3B%20Roubini%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20you%20remember%2C%202022%2C%20when%20yields%20were%20going%20higher%2C%20S%26amp%3BP%20fell%2015%25%2C%20Nasdaq%20fell%2020%25%2C%20and%20growth%20stocks%20fell%20by%2040%25%20or%20even%20more.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoubini%20makes%20some%20compelling%20points%20about%20the%20direction%20inflation%20could