d%2C%20a%20demographer%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Virginia%2C%20found%20that%2063%25%20of%20rural%20counties%20or%20counties%20in%20small%20metros%20experienced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.coopercenter.org%2Fresearch%2Fyoung-adults-fuel-revival-small-towns-rural-areas%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreases%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20populations%20of%2025-%20to%2044-year-olds%20between%202020%20and%202023%2C%20compared%20to%2027%25%20between%202010%20and%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENorthern%20Georgia%2C%20the%20Mountain%20West%2C%20and%20New%20England%20were%20rural%20regions%20with%20particularly%20strong%20population%20growth%20among%20young%20Americans.%20The%2010%20counties%20that%20saw%20the%20biggest%20influxes%20of%20younger%20adults%20were%20largely%20rural%3B%20the%20most%20populated%20of%20all%20of%20those%20areas%20is%20Hays%20County%2C%20Texas%2C%20in%20the%20suburbs%20of%20Austin%2C%20which%20had%20a%20population%20of%20around%20280%2C500%20in%202023.%20Musselshell%20County%2C%20which%20is%20the%20least%20populous%2C%20had%20just%205%2C308%20people%20as%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F2YLUs%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Top%2010%20counties%20Americans%2025%20to%2044%20migrated%20to%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22489%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20big%20shift%20from%20pre-pandemic%20patterns%3A%20From%201980%20to%202020%2C%20white-collar%20workers%20increasingly%20moved%20into%20densely%20populated%20areas%2C%20per%20Lombard's%20analysis.%20That%20trend%20was%20expected%20to%20continue%20%E2%80%94%20until%20the%20pandemic%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20remote%20work.%20Since%202020%2C%20Lombard%20found%2C%20rural%20areas%20and%20smaller%20cities%20have%20attracted%20that%20younger%20workforce%20at%20the%20highest%20rate%20in%20nearly%20a%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FVlcp3%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Change%20in%20population%20ages%2025%20to%2044%2C%202020-2023%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22477%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EJeannie%20Steele%2C%20a%20real-estate%20broker%20in%20Townsend%2C%20Montana%2C%20has%20seen%20an%20influx%20of%20young%20people.%20Broadwater%20County%2C%20with%20about%208%2C000%20residents%2C%20was%20the%20third-fastest-growing%20county%20for%20Americans%20ages%2025%20to%2044%2C%20Lombard's%20analysis%20found.%20Townsend%20is%20located%20about%2030%20miles%20from%20Helena%2C%20though%20Steele%20said%20many%20commute%20to%20Bozeman%20or%20Three%20Forks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteele%20said%20she%20previously%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Econsidered%20her%20area%20a%20retirement%20hub.%20However%2C%20the%20construction%20of%20a%20new%20elementary%20school%20starting%20in%202019%20brought%20many%20younger%20families%2C%20particularly%20some%20working%20in%20construction%2C%20mining%2C%20or%20medicine.%20Many%20are%20moving%20from%20Washington%2C%20California%2C%20and%20Minnesota%2C%20Steele%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20here%20that%20come%20and%20have%20this%20vision%20of%20homesteading%2C%26quot%3B%20Steele%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20want%20to%20grow%20their%20own%20food.%20They%20want%20to%20have%20chickens%20and%20gardens.%20Interestingly%20enough%2C%20though%2C%20all%20those%20things%20in%20our%20environment%20are%20difficult.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Custer%20County%2C%20Colorado%20%E2%80%94%20the%20area%20that's%20seen%20the%20highest%20net%20percent%20increase%20of%2025%20to%2044-year-olds%20%E2%80%94%2028-year-old%20Arrott%20Smith%20has%20seen%20many%20more%20nice%20cars%20driving%20around%20as%20younger%2C%20well-off%20remote%20workers%20move%20into%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20most%20part%2C%20that's%20kind%20of%20a%20weird%20juxtaposition%20because%20it%20is%20a%20very%20working-class%20county%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmith%2C%20the%20manager%20and%20a%20roaster%20at%20local%20haunt%20Peregrine%20Coffee%2C%20said%20that%20the%20area%20has%20traditionally%20skewed%20older%20%E2%80%94%20but%20saw%20a%20big%20influx%20of%20younger%20workers%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years.%20Smith%20said%20that%20the%20area's%20newer%20residents%20are%20buying%20homes%20even%20as%20costs%20have%20gone%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20me%20it's%20more%20like%20the%20people%20that%20are%20moving%20here%20have%20a%20romanticized%20version%20of%20what%20it%20is%20to%20live%20up%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222e61d1f9-3773-42a7-ae93-3d623dfb33f7%5C%22%3EGoing%20rural%20can%20be%20challenging%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEconomist%20Jed%20Kolko%20said%20that%2C%20with%20the%20proliferation%20of%20remote%20work%2C%20Americans%20moved%20out%20of%20bigger%20urban%20areas%20into%20nearby%20suburbs%20or%20smaller%20towns.%20But%20headwinds%20in%20some%20occupations%20might%20slow%20down%20the%20influx%20of%20newcomers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20unemployment%20rises%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20kinds%20of%20occupations%20where%20remote%20work%20is%20more%20common%2C%20employers%20might%20be%20more%20able%20to%20insist%20on%20workers%20spending%20more%20days%20in%20the%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20Kolko%20said.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20that%20doesn't%20cause%20people%20to%20reverse%20the%20moves%20that%20they%20made%20during%20or%20after%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20could%20still%20slow%20down%20that%20trend%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20in%20areas%20that%20have%20seen%20a%20rush%20of%20new%20residents%20like%20Townsend%2C%20Kolko%20said%20it's%20key%20for%20housing%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20demand.%20If%20not%2C%20affordability%20challenges%20from%20big%20cities%20could%20spread%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20challenges%20confront%20the%20residents%20reshaping%20these%20areas.%20Steele%20said%20many%20people%20moved%20to%20her%20part%20of%20Montana%20after%20the%20TV%20series%20%26quot%3BYellowstone%26quot%3B%20aired%2C%20though%20she's%20seen%20many%20younger%20people%20regret%20their%20moves.%20She%20said%20many%20don't%20anticipate%20the%20challenges%20of%20living%20in%20a%20more%20remote%20part%20of%20the%20US%2C%20such%20as%20navigating%20storms%2C%20buying%20goods%20in%20bulk%2C%20or%20dealing%20with%20isolation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20rentals%20have%20gone%20really%20fast%2C%20Steele%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20rents%2C%20on%20average%2C%20have%20increased%20from%20about%20%24750%20in%202019%20to%20well%20over%20%241%2C000%20monthly.%20A%20more%20stark%20comparison%20is%20some%20of%20the%20county's%20single-family%20homes%2C%20many%20of%20which%20were%20built%20in%20the%20late%201970s%20and%20early%201980s%3B%20while%20they%20sold%20for%20about%20%24100%2C000%20in%202017%2C%20they%20range%20from%20%24390%2C000%20to%20%24400%2C000%20today%2C%20Steele%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHousing%20affordability%20pushed%20Solitaire%20Miles%2C%20a%20Gen%20X%20musician%2C%20to%20move%20from%20Chicago%20to%20northwestern%20Indiana%20in%202013.%20Miles%20and%20her%20husband%20lived%20in%20the%20Chicago%20area%20for%20about%2013%20years.%20While%20they%20were%20gainfully%20employed%2C%20she%20said%2C%20they%20weren't%20earning%20enough%20to%20live%20comfortably%20while%20renting.%20They%20couldn't%20afford%20a%20home%20in%20Illinois%2C%20especially%20with%20high%20property%20taxes.%20But%20in%20Indiana%2C%20they%20found%20a%20home%20with%20three-quarters%20of%20an%20acre%20of%20land%20just%2050%20miles%20from%20Chicago%20for%20under%20%24200%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiles%20loves%20having%20the%20space.%20A%20quieter%20pace%20of%20living%20has%20helped%20stimulate%20her%20creativity%20and%20her%20at-home%20border%20collie%20rescue%20%E2%80%94%20they%20currently%20have%20five%20of%20their%20own%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228129%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Solitaire%20Miles%20and%20dogs%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675c671852dd0818d1a712d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226263%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESolitaire%20Miles%20and%20dogs.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Solitaire%20Miles%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20area%20has%20changed%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%3B%20the%20pandemic%20also%20fractured%20her%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20Covid%2C%20everything%20just%20kind%20of%20went%20downhill.%20So%20many%20people%20died%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20elderly%20died%2C%20or%20they%20left%20and%20they%20moved%20south%2C%26quot%3B%20Miles%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20glad%20they%20ended%20up%20buying%20out%20there%2C%20and%20if%20and%20when%20they%20choose%20to%20sell%2C%20they'll%20make%20a%20tidy%20profit.%20Even%20so%2C%20though%2C%20the%20move%20came%20with%20its%20own%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20hard.%20I%20had%20the%20gym%20that%20I%20loved%20and%20the%20spas%20and%20my%20beauty%20salon%20and%20the%20restaurants%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20our%20friends%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20I%20did%20make%20friends%20here%2C%20but%20it%20took%20time%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20go%20to%20places%20where%20I%20knew%20they%20would%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Voss%2C%20the%20real-estate%20agent%2C%20it%20took%20him%20time%20to%20acclimate%20to%20the%20South.%20As%20a%20gay%20man%2C%20he%20noticed%20more%20hostility%20toward%20his%20community%2C%20though%20he%20said%20many%20in%20Dawsonville%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-that-surprised-me-moving-from-city-to-small-town-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappreciated%20his%20advocacy%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He's%20enjoying%20rural%20Georgia%20for%20the%20time%20being%20but%20anticipates%20splitting%20his%20time%20with%20Hawaii%20in%20a%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGeorgia%20is%20beautiful%2C%20I%20love%20it.%20It's%20so%20great%20for%20so%20many%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Voss%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20for%20me%2C%20because%20of%20the%20mentality%20of%20the%20people%20here%2C%20I%20just%20don't%20see%20myself%20staying%20full-time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20moved%20to%20a%20rural%20area%20and%20regretted%20it%20(or%20loved%20it)%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejkaplan%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ensheidlower%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-americans-move-from-cities-rural-areas-millennials-gen-x-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734168662000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675cb029cf8d1359a2e00f89%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-americans-move-from-cities-rural-areas-millennials-gen-x-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20young%20Americans%20moved%20to%20rural%20areas.%20It's%20a%20big%20shift.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan%2CNoah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-americans-move-from-cities-rural-areas-millennials-gen-x-2024-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C