C%20a%20mom-of-two%20who%20founded%20the%20fitness%20app%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbthemethod.com%2Fpages%2Fmeet-lia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EB%20The%20Method%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20means%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flow-impact-exercise-build-core-strength-muscle-stability-coach-advice-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elow-impact%20exercise%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBartha%20told%20Business%20Insider%20she%20spent%20her%2020s%20and%20early%2030s%20pushing%20her%20body%20to%20the%20limit%20doing%20high-intensity%20cardio%20and%20teaching%20Pilates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBartha%20knew%20she%20needed%20a%20change%20when%20she%20hit%20her%20mid-30s%2C%20after%20she%20had%20kids.%20She%20was%20looking%20ahead%20at%20how%20she%20wanted%20to%20feel%20in%20the%20long-term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20trained%20and%20taught%20that%20way%20for%20so%20long%2C%20I%20started%20to%20feel%20myself%20kind%20of%20plateauing%20and%20getting%20bored%20because%20it%20was%20so%20rigid.%20I%20felt%20like%20it%20wasn't%20necessarily%20intuitive%20in%20how%20my%20body%20was%20aging%2C%26quot%3B%20Bartha%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20in%202018%2C%20she%20developed%20her%20own%20method%2C%20an%20online%20fitness%20brand%20that%20incorporates%20Pilates%20along%20with%20other%20wellness%20techniques%20such%20as%20breath-work%20and%20gentle%20movements%20to%20subtly%20tone%20muscle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20from%20classic%20Pilates%2C%20and%20big%20equipment%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftried-reformer-pilates-loved-it-would-do-again-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereformers%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20a%20better%20fit%20for%20her%20body%20as%20she%20got%20older%20%E2%80%94%20and%20drew%20in%20thousands%20of%20subscribers%20globally.%20Bartha%20has%20worked%20with%20celebrity%20clients%20like%20Aubrey%20Plaza%2C%20Cynthia%20Erivo%2C%20Ego%20Nwodim%2C%20and%20model%20Martha%20Hunt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20thinking%20in%20this%20bigger%20way%20of%2C%20how%20is%20supporting%20my%20body%20for%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%3F%26quot%3B%20Bartha%2C%20now%2041%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20mom%20of%20two%20girls%2C%20so%20I%20have%20this%20job%20of%20working%20out%20and%20I'm%20teaching%20and%20then%20I'm%20doing%20the%20business%20side%20and%20then%20I%20have%20to%20take%20on%20this%20extra%20shift%20of%20taking%20care%20of%20them%20and%20feeding%20them.%20I%20think%20the%20exercise%20really%20has%20to%20help%20you%20mentally.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2286e06e9a-cfb0-4745-a4de-690caba347e5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E10%20minutes%20is%20plenty%20of%20time%20to%20work%20out%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20younger%20athlete%20and%20dancer%2C%20Bartha%20said%20she%20spent%20hours%20on%20cardio%20or%20intense%20exercise%20to%20stay%20in%20shape%2C%20but%20adjusting%20her%20workouts%20to%20a%20packed%20schedule%20has%20taught%20her%20to%20do%20more%20with%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20kind%20of%20just%20doing%20what%20everybody%20else%20was%20doing.%20I%20was%20like%2C%20OK%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20get%20on%20the%20treadmill%20and%20just%20walk%20or%20run%20forever%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20she%20often%20works%20out%20for%20less%20than%20an%20hour%2C%20and%20designs%20workouts%20that%20are%20just%20as%20challenging%20and%20effective%20in%2020%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20benefit%20of%20shorter%20sessions%20is%20that%20it's%20easier%20to%20commit%20to%20them%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%2045%20minutes%20or%20an%20hour%20all%20the%20time.%20If%20you're%20giving%20yourself%2010%20minutes%20a%20day%20very%20consistently%2C%20you'll%20see%20huge%20benefits%2C%26quot%3B%20Bartha%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e5ddd8b3-c20c-48b6-a815-c36288e835ef%5C%22%3ELow-impact%20exercise%20is%20a%20gentler%20way%20to%20train%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20shift%20for%20Bartha%20was%20learning%20that%20exhaustion%20and%20sweatiness%20isn't%20the%20best%20indicator%20of%20a%20good%20workout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20have%20to%20go%20through%20an%20aggressive%20workout%20that%20leaves%20you%20very%20sore%20and%20fatigued%20to%20have%20all%20of%20the%20benefits%20of%20exercise%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELow-impact%20workouts%20like%20Pilates%20tend%20to%20emphasize%20slow%2C%20controlled%20movements%20instead%20of%20fast%2C%20explosive%20techniques.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20they're%20easier%20on%20the%20joints%2C%20and%20don't%20take%20as%20much%20recovery%20time%20afterward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELow-impact%20techniques%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ffitness%2Fisometric-exercises%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eisometric%20movements%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20many%20of%20the%20same%20benefits%20as%20higher-intensity%20training%20in%20helping%20to%20build%20strength%20and%20muscle.%20They%20can%20also%20improve%20factors%20linked%20to%20longevity%2C%20such%20as%20stability%20and%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20think%20of%20the%20body%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that's%20where%20low-impact%20is%20just%20so%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20Bartha%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3ad254d-fe7a-438d-be42-aedb9bfe3236%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsistency%20is%20key%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBartha%20said%20she%20fell%20into%20the%20trap%20of%20pushing%20too%20hard%20instead%20of%20developing%20an%20enjoyable%2C%20sustainable%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20most%20common%20mistakes%20that%20people%20have%20in%20terms%20of%20fitness%20is%20just%20getting%20through%20it%20to%20get%20through%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20listening%20to%20her%20body%20and%20taking%20it%20easier%20led%20to%20better%20results%2C%20with%20less%20work%2C%20because%20the