vises%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20best%20time%20to%20visit%20is%20winter.%20Do%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F287202%2Fgulab-jamun-indian-sweet-uttar-pradesh-food-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etry%20the%3Cem%3E%20gulab%20jamuns%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Indian%20sweet%20made%20with%20%3Cem%3Ekoya%3C%2Fem%3E)%20here.%20They%20are%20silky%20smooth%20and%20warm.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20Rajesh%20Samosa%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20usual%20versions%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Eare%20popular%2C%20their%20counterparts%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20the%20%3Cem%3Emaha%20samosa%20%3C%2Fem%3E(big%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20the%20mini%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20have%20a%20comparable%20fan%20following.%20The%20latter%20finds%20expression%20in%20the%20menu%20at%20Rajesh%20Samosa%20opposite%20Scindia%20House%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Connaught%20Place.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnubhav%20Sapra%20of%20Delhi%20Food%20Walks%20stumbled%20upon%20it%20on%20one%20of%20his%20walks%20and%20since%20then%20has%20been%20an%20ardent%20fan.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20bite-sized%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Epack%20a%20spicy%20punch%20and%20are%20ideal%20for%20a%20snack%20you%20can%20grab%20on%20the%20go.%20Their%20crispy%20shells%20and%20warm%20fillings%20are%20perfect%20for%20an%20afternoon%20pick-me-up%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F8xWgyXlo9MI%3Fsi%3DpaS8eEkKQrgxDtVr%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%2C%20Anubhav%20encourages%20you%20to%20wander%20around.%20The%20area%20is%20known%20for%20its%20gastronomy.%20Delectable%20evidence%20can%20be%20found%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Echole%20bhature%3C%2Fem%3E%20(chickpea%20gravy%20served%20with%20Indian%20flatbread)%2C%20fresh%20fruit%20%3Cem%3Echaat%3C%2Fem%3E%20(street%20food)%2C%20cooling%20%3Cem%3Edahi%20bhalle%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20dish%20that%20combines%20fluffy%20lentil%20dumplings%20soaked%20in%20creamy%20%3Cem%3Eyogurt%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20topped%20with%20spices%20and%20%3Cem%3Echutneys%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F259515%2Findian-food-recipes-pakora-map-of-india-cuisine-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Epaneer%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebread%20%3Cem%3Epakoda%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E(fried%20snack%20with%20cottage%20cheese).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E6.%20The%20Embassy%20Restaurant%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmbassy%20is%20independent%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20restaurant%20started%20in%201948.%20And%20food%20blogger%20Anushka%20Goel%E2%80%99s%20family%20are%20loyalists.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20parents%20introduced%20me%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehere%20when%20I%20was%20a%20kid.%20What%20excited%20me%20more%20than%20anything%20else%20was%20their%20size%3B%20they%20were%20so%20huge!%20I%20remember%20the%20first%20time%20I%20tasted%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20the%20huge%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F313009%2Fbengaluru-couple-nidhi-shikhar-start-samosa-singh-brand-of-crispy-chaat-snacks%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejumbo-sized%20snack%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20more%20than%20what%20my%20mom%20and%20I%20could%20finish%20together!%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2Fsamosa-in-delhi-2-1732281499.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22